<SLUG> BC-NY-CINEMA-SHOOTING-1STLD-WRITETHRU-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
3 SHOT IN CROWDED BROOKLYN CINEMA; POLICE CITE GANG TENSIONS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (expands with additional details)   (bl)  
 By ANDY NEWMAN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Three men were shot and wounded in a crowded movie
theater in Flatbush, Brooklyn, on Friday night by a man who then
fled the moviehouse, police said.
</P>
<P>
   A police spokesman said that the gunfire erupted after a dispute
over seating, but a senior officer at the scene said that the
shootings appeared to be gang related.
</P>
<P>
   The shootings, which occurred around 10 p.m., 15 minutes into an
opening-night screening of the new Eddie Murphy movie ``Life,''
sent hundreds patrons flooding out of the Kenmore Quad Theater onto
Church Avenue outside, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
   Two of victims were in surgery at Kings County Hospital Center
on Friday night, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   One man, 19, was in critical condition after being shot in the
back. Another, also 19, who was shot three times in the chest, was
in serious condition, and a third 19-year-old was stable with a
wound in the back, said Jerry Varson, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Two men who were in the lobby at the time of the shootings said
they believed the gunfire was gang related and that audience
members were shouting out ``Crips'' and ``Bloods'' just before the
movie started.
</P>
<P>
   A senior officer at the scene agreed that gangs seemed to be
tied to the shootings but that beyond that it was difficult to say
what prompted them.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not even sure if the three people shot were on the same
team, so to speak, because the theater was so dark,'' the officer
said. The officer said the investigation was hampered by the fact
that most of the witnesses ran out.
</P>
<P>
   One of the men who was in the lobby said that he heard four or
five shots coming from inside the theater.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was like all at once _ pap pap pap pap,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   After that, he said, ``it was just like a stampede. Whenever
somebody pulls out a gun, all you can do is run.''
</P>
<P>
   Although the screening of ``Life,'' a prison comedy starring
Murphy and Martin Lawrence, was canceled, the other three movies
being screened at the Kenmore, an old brick theater on a commercial
strip just west of Flatbush Avenue, continued without interruption.
</P>
<P>
   Several peope who had watched the movie ``The Matrix'' emerged
afterward into the surreal real-life scene of a lobby criss-crossed
with yellow crime-scene tape and crawling with uniformed officers.
</P>
<P>
   O'Linda Stewart, 23, said she overheard some men who came late
into ``The Matrix'' talking about bullets, but thought nothing of
it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I heard these guys saying there were mad shots going on, but I
thought it was in the movie,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-17-99 0110EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
