elaborate celebrations of the 50th anniversary of the communist
state this fall, Beijing's city planners enacted what must be one
of the world's strangest traffic laws: a local ban on hatchbacks
during daylight hours. By Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
<P>
   MALAYSIA-ANWAR (Kuala Lumpur) _ Dr. Wan Azizah Wan Ismail has
been thrust into the center of Malaysia's gathering political
storm. The wife of the ousted and imprisoned former Deputy Prime
Minister Ibrahim Anwar has formed a political party to topple Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   ITALY-U.S.-JETS (Washington) _ With the U.S. strictly observing
Italian rules on low-altitude flights since a Marine jet severed a
ski gondola cable last year, killing 20 people, Italy is now
unsuitable for some essential training, a U.S. admiral said. By
Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
