   NY-EMBRYO-MIXUP (New York) _ In a case of mixed-up embryos that
caused a Staten Island woman who underwent in vitro fertilization
to give birth to two sons of different races, a state inquiry has
concluded that the embryologist knew he had implanted the wrong
eggs but failed to tell anyone because he did not think the
fertilized eggs would develop. By Jim Yardley.
