<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990417.0047 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-17 10:35 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3816 &Cx1f; var-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NATO-ANTIWAR-REVIEW-9     04-17 0960
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NATO-ANTIWAR-REVIEW-900(2TAKES)-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE DOVES OF YESTERYEAR FLY OFF TO A DIFFERENT WAR 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (jt)  
 By CRAIG R. WHITNEY    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRUSSELS, Belgium _ Think of NATO's 50th anniversary summit
meeting as the first war council of the Cold War's anti-warriors.
</P>
<P>
   Leaders who had reputations for avoiding the draft or
