 UNDATED: the brain .'' 
<TEXT>
<P>
   McEwen's work offers clues to how stressful experience might
eventually translate into physical illness, and how treatments that
reduce stress might prove beneficial to health. Just as blood
pressure and heart rate adjust when a person moves from a lying to
a standing position, the body's approach to stress is
