in your head, don't believe them,'' Spiegel said, ``but if they
tell you that it might help you cope with the disease once you've
got it, and that it might have some effect on disease course, as
well as quality of life, that might well be true.''
</P>
<P>
   Similarly, Dr. Joshua Smyth, lead author of last week's asthma
and rheumatoid arthritis study, cautioned that, ``The worst
