<HEADLINE>
POLITICAL PROPS AND CAMPAIGNS THAT TAKE OFF, OR CRASH 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
(jt) 
 By DAVID WALLIS    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Last week in Washington, the Titanic was involved in another
disaster. Just before advocates for senior citizens planned to
hoist on stage a 24-foot cabin cruiser bearing the slogan
``Medicare Vouchers Are a Titanic Mistake,'' the Capitol Police
sunk their efforts. Judging the symbolic Titanic too heavy for the
