<P>
   FBC-BAMA-QB _ TUSCALOOSA, Ala. _ Sophomore Andrew Zow fared
quite well as a redshirt freshman quarterback. In Alabama's new
wide open offense, Zow threw for 1,969 yards and 11 touchdowns and
is presence made the Crimson Tide attack less predictable. But Zow
is now locked in a battle for his job with redshirt freshman Tyler
Watts, the highly touted recruit who sat out last season. No matter
who wins the job, Alabama will be able to move the ball in 1999.
Passing coordinator Charlie Stubbs, who put in the attack last
season, turned down a head coaching job to return to Tuscaloosa an
complete the job of building this offense. So things are looking up
at Alabama, but the Tide is still a year away from competing for
the SEC's Western Division (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18. MOVED
</P>
