<P>
   RUN-BOSTON-WOMEN _ BOSTON _ As Fatuma Roba, gold medalist from
Atlanta Olympics, returns to defend her Boston Marathon title in
the 103rd edition, but it wasn't that long ago that women weren't
welcome on the course. Women officially didn't join the race until
1972. Five years earlier, an official attempted to physically
remove Kathrine Switzer from the course in 1967. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-QUAIL _ The Georgia Wildlife Resources Division has
accomplished some near miracles in the past; bringing back a deer
herd that had dwindled to less than 5,000 to more than a million
today and accomplishing a similar feat with the almost extinct wild
turkey. The department's next mission is to restore the quail
population and this one might qualify as a true miracle if
accomplished. The key to quail restoration isn't more birds, it's
more land, Georgia's most precious commodity. (Mitchell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
