<HEADLINE>
TEXAN SEES MISERY OF REFUGEES
</HEADLINE>
 By JACK DOUGLAS JR. 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Former Fort Worth Mayor Hugh Parmer, just
back from a six-day tour of Albanian refugee camps in the war-torn
Balkans, said he heard repeated stories of murder and rape and saw
tears in the eyes of everyone who crossed into friendly territory.
</P>
<P>
   There are few expressions of hope that the war will soon be over
for the thousands of refugees fleeing Serbian forces, Parmer said
Saturday in Fort Worth.
</P>
<P>
   ``I talked to two young women, well-dressed, middle class, early
30s ... who looked like they could have come from Fort Worth, but
with tears running down their faces as they pointed back over the
border, saying: `They took everything we had, our money, our
jewelry, our documents, everything except our suitcase,' '' Parmer
said.
</P>
<P>
   Parmer lives in Washington, where he is assistant administrator
for humanitarian response at the Agency for International
Development. He toured refugee camps in Macedonia and Albania, and
returned to Washington on Thursday to report on the progress of
relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
   Parmer arrived in Fort Worth yesterday to attend the 87th
birthday party tomorrow for his father, Quay Parmer.
</P>
<P>
   Conditions are particularly deplorable at one Albanian camp,
Parmer said. ``There were at least 20,000 people just living in the
open: no tents, no roofs, maybe just sheets of plastic draped over
their wagons,'' he said. While there, Parmer said, ``I got a lot of
stories of murders, rapes, family members shot down in front of the
eyes of their children.''
</P>
<P>
   Parmer said he watched as scores of Kosovo residents stepped
from their homeland into Albania. ``Every person began to weep when
they walked across the border,'' he said. ``All I could do is shake
their hand and say, `It's OK. You're safe now.' ''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
